SIMPLE: pussy
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pussy
<hw>Pussy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Dim. of
<ets>puss</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A pet name for a cat; also, an
endearing name for a girl.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A catkin of the pussy willow.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>The game of tipcat; -- also called <altname>pussy
cat</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Pussy willow</b></col> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>, <cd>any kind of
willow having large cylindrical catkins clothed with long glossy hairs,
especially the American <spn>Salix discolor</spn>; -- called also
<altname>glaucous willow</altname>, and <altname>swamp
willow</altname>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pussy</ent>⟦br⟧

